[0.010, "o", "\u001b[1;37mVibeFrame inside Claude Code — natural-language → vibe CLI\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2mNo setup. Claude discovers vibe via --help and drives it from Bash.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.007, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m── live Claude Code session ──\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.505, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m❯\u001b[0m \u001b[1;37mI have the 'vibe' CLI installed (vibeframe video editor). Use it to scaffold a small 16:9 scene project named 'cc-demo' (6s duration), then add an announcement scene named 'hello' with the headline 'Hello from Claude Code' (skip audio and image). Then lint it. Use --help when needed to discover flags. Brief summary at the end.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[1.775, "o", "\u001b[2mclaude code · session start · Bash tool only · ANTHROPIC_API_KEY set\u001b[0m\r\n"]
